    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Genus containing 43 species of annual and perennial herbs native to Middle East and Asia. It is best known for the widely cultivated member, C. arietinum, chickpea.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
